author: Retro Game Corps
description:
The latest Beelinik mini PC (SER 9 Pro) isn't revolutionary, but it packs a punch for its size, has excellent cooling, and is somehow cheaper than their previous release.  Let's discuss why this is the best $500 mini PC you can find right now.

Beelink direct: https://tidd.ly/4qEToI4
Also on Amazon (use the coupon!): https://amzn.to/4nvh92m

The SER9 (non-Pro) has the same CPU, RAM, and storage, but without the mic array: https://amzn.to/4ogzoKf

RGC Mini PC spreadsheet: https://tinyurl.com/RGCminiPC
Jim's music: https://ourghosts.bandcamp.com/
Aoostar AG02 eGPU dock: https://amzn.to/433hou9

This was a review unit sent to me by the manufacturer.  All opinions are my own, they did not see this review ahead of time, and no money was exchanged in any way.
